Body: Description: We are getting a malware notification from this EPP file: DeviceHarddiskVolume3Program FilesCoSoSysEndpoint Protectori386Wow64ProcHelper.exe hash: d0610cf543b5779ec42b0ce5177305853aa8837b Please confirm this is the correct file from your platform.
What We've Learned Updated: The file Wow64ProcHelper.exe from the EPP Client was reported as malware

Next Steps Updated: Waiting for R&D to confirm if this is the correct file or not.
And if so, to find out why it was reported as malware.

Next Steps Updated: The file is the correct one, but it belongs to an older version of the EPP Client.
I asked for a remote session in order to update the EPP Server to the latest version
